The new Walther SOFTCOIL ™ gas-delayed blowback technology works to make the CCP an excellent concealed carry firearm.How Walther SOFTCOIL ™ Technology Makes This Pistol A Must-HaveThe CCP’s SOFTCOIL™ gas-delayed blowback system uses gas pressure from the ignited cartridge by directing it through a small port in the barrel in front of the chamber to slow down and delay the rearward motion of the slide. This is accomplished by means of a piston contained inside of a cylinder located under the barrel that opposes the rearward motion of the slide until the gas pressure has declined after the bullet has left the barrel. postcontent:
London Bridge Trading 6094A Medium sized plate carrier.   One of the most comfortable carriers I've ever worn.
This is meant to fit medium sized ESAPI plates.  Plate carriers are sized to your plates, not body type.  As a general rule, you want to wear plates just big enough to cover your vitals.  Typically that's about 1-2 "sizes" down from your shirt size.  If you wear XL, then you want medium plates.  If you wear L, then you want either medium or possibly small plates , ect.   Not always the case, but generally true if you have a "normal" body size.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Springfield SAR-8 (HK91/G3 variant)
postcontent:
The HK G3/91 is one of the most iconic guns of the 20th century, and for good reason. HK branded ones can go for well over 3k, and even the cheaper clones made on parts kits run around 1k. In the 80's and 90's Springfield wanted to expand their selection without the effort of designing a new gun, so they struck a deal with HK to resale their HK 91 firearms in the US. These were all new parts, made in an HK factory by HK technicians. After the import ban in 89, they had the new parts shipped in, and assembled on a US made receiver in the Springfield Armory shop.
Arguably the best thing about these rifles, other than being as close to an HK as a clone gets, is that they SA lifetime warranty follows them! If you ever manage to kill it they will replace it with their equivalent model, the M1A1!
This one has a low round count, 6 all steel German made 20 round mags and 3 super hard to find steel 30 round mags, that go for around $80 a piece in surplus condition. It also has an illuminated 1-4 Target Sports scope. These are hard to find guns that shoot as well as the original but you can actually enjoy them without losing value on every shot.
$1100/shipped or $950/shipped with just the 20 rounders. FTF in NoVA ok w/ proper good guy creds. Also open to local trades for interesting stuff (Sig's, Beretta's, no Glocks pls)

title: For Sale:  VEPR 7.62x54R Wood Stock 20" Barrel at Ventura Munitions
postcontent: The semi-auto hunting rifles VEPR are designed for medium-sized and big games. AK-based design and construction of the rifles provides a reliable operation of parts and mechanisms as well as high-grade shooting in various weather and climatic conditions. The rifles can be used in a wide temperature range (from -50 F up to +120 F).  VEPR's parts are manufactured using the same equipment as the very well known lightweight machinegun RPK. Its extra heavy duty receiver and hammer-forged barrel provide much better accuracy and durability. A chrome-lined barrel with chrome-lined chamber and bore along with walnut stocks make these rifles very different from other AK-based rifles available in the US market  The rifles come with adjustable open sighting devices and a rail for a scope mount attached to the left side of the receiver.
